resources.string: The historic English Landscape Garden style grounds, designed by Thomas Goldney 3rd, include an orangery, gothic tower and grotto. The Goldney Hall gardens encompass a 10-acre site and are known for their notable five follies: Ornamental Canal, Gothic Tower, Rotunda, Mock Bastion, Shell-lined Grotto. A sixth folly, the Octagon, consisted of a two-story summer house located where L block stands today. While the exact date of the removal of the Octagon is not known, it is missing from plans which date to 1864.
